# Changelog and versioning

This project documents changes in [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) format and uses [Semantic Versioning 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html) for version numbers. Follow those specs when adding entries, cutting releases, or editing `[project].version` in `pyproject.toml`.

## Keep a Changelog (summary)

- Use the standard change categories, in this order: **Added**, **Changed**, **Deprecated**, **Removed**, **Fixed**, **Security** (omit empty sections). Within an existing release, match the file’s current section order; for **new** release blocks, use this order.
- Newest release sections go **at the top** (after any `[Unreleased]` block if you add one).
- Each release: `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD` (ISO 8601 date). Link definitions at the bottom of the file are optional but should stay in sync with tagged releases if present.
- Entries are user-facing, imperative bullets (what changed for consumers), not commit dumps.

## SemVer 2.0.0 (summary)

- **MAJOR** — incompatible API/behavior; **MINOR** — backward-compatible functionality; **PATCH** — backward-compatible fixes.
- Pre-release: e.g. `1.0.0-alpha.1` / `1.0.0-beta.2` / `1.0.0-rc.1` with identifiers after a hyphen. Build metadata: `+build` (e.g. `1.0.0+20260422`).
- The same `X.Y.Z` must appear in the new `## [X.Y.Z]` heading and in `pyproject.toml` `[project].version` for that release (unless the project uses dynamic version only from tags—if so, do not leave them inconsistent).

## References

- [Keep a Changelog 1.1.0](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/) — full rules and philosophy.
- [SemVer 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html) — version precedence and syntax.
